RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AUNT OPAL sent clear, continued clear under a strong aggressive ride, entered turn clear, drifted out in upper stretch, kept to task and held rivals safely at bay. ISLAND LIFE stalked pace two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn swung widest into the lane, rallied well in the seven path to get up for second at the wire. FLASHY PASS chased clear leader two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, angled in when winner drifted out in upper stretch, gained and flattened out final hundred yards and was nailed for second at the final jump. ROCK N ROLL SONG away cleanly, had to take up sharply when QUEEN VERRAZANO lugged out, settled into stride midway through the backstretch, took the turn in the two path, split rivals entering the lane and kept on gamely while being outclosed. QUEEN VERRAZANO broke in, lugged out three paths early and caused ROCK N ROLL SONG to take up, went back along the inside for the turn, eased out and angled out four wide into the lane, made mild progress until flattening out the final sixteenth. CROWN KITTEN away cleanly, settled off the pace and along the rail on the backstretch, continued to save ground on the turn and failed to respond in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Queen Verrazano
ENTRY.COMMENT: lugged out early, stalked inside, angled 4wide, flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Aunt Opal
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent clear, drifted out upper stretch, held safely

ENTRY.NAME: Island Life
ENTRY.OWNER: RD Race Stable Inc and Monterroso Pocasangre Maria Jose

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 2wide, angled in upper stretch, nailed 2nd wire

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden Races And Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Considere d In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NENE ROMANO dueled for the lead along the inside on the backstretch, continued to duel on the turn, entered lane holding a slim margin, summoned all she had and refused to be denied in a gallant effort. RUN AUNTIE T RUN dueled two wide throughout, kept on gamely and just could not get by the game winner. B B GUN BULLSEYE sat off a duel two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, launched bid three wide and made mild progress under a drive. AUNTIE BEV chased dueling rivals along the inside on the backstretch, continued to save ground on the turn, made progress in the lane but not enough to improve position. MY SWEET MARY fractious and reared inside the gate, broke out and bumped rival at the start, stalked contested pace three wide on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn, entered lane in the three path and needed more while making mild progress. QUIET FOREST bumped back by inside rival at the start, rider chose to stay well off the rail, took the turn four wide, failed to make any headway on the turn and lacked a bid in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: My Sweet Mary
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious, broke out/bumped start, stalked 3wide, needed more 4p
